  "title": "Manager – Corporate Outreach & Executive Education",
  "description": "<p><strong>Office Location:</strong> 10 Hyderabad Rd, HortPark, Singapore 119579</p>\n<p><strong>Reporting to:</strong> Head of Executive Education / CEO</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Identify, engage, and convert corporate clients for executive education programs (customized and open enrolment) </li>\n  <li>Manage end-to-end sales cycle: lead generation, pitching, proposal development, follow-up, and closure </li>\n  <li>Build long-term relationships with HR, L&amp;D, and senior leadership across industries </li>\n  <li>Collaborate with academic and program teams to design relevant learning solutions</li>\n  <li>Represent the institution at business events, forums, and conferences</li>\n  <li>Maintain accurate and timely sales reporting in CRM system</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Key Performance Indicators (KPIs):</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Sales Targets:</strong> Achievement of quarterly and annual sales targets</li>\n  <li><strong>Lead Generation:</strong> Minimum number of qualified B2B leads/prospects</li>\n  <li><strong>Client Engagements:</strong> meaningful meetings or presentations conducted with decision-makers</li>\n  <li><strong>Client Relations:</strong> Maintain relations with existing clients and new ones</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor’s degree 2 to 3 years of relevant B2B sales experience, preferably in executive education, corporate training, or consulting </li>\n  <li>Excellent communication, presentation, and client management skills </li>\n  <li>Strong network within the HR/L&amp;D ecosystem is a plus</li>\n  <li>Goal-driven, proactive, and comfortable in a target-based environment</li>\n</ul>",
